  "body": "Instead of displaying keycard in the list of the keycards displayed in `Settings -> Keycard`, we should display there just a keycards containing different keypairs. That means if any of displayed keypairs is migrated/backed up to more than a one keycard the list of certain keypair and list of keycard that keypair is migrated to should be displayed in the keycard details view, which is actually this screen:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/idUoxN7OIW2Jpp3PMJ1Rl8/%E2%9A%99%EF%B8%8F-Settings-%7C-Desktop?node-id=3589%3A157439\r\n\r\nThere should be no checkbox/radio button selecting the keycard we want to take an action for (any action from the list of actions available from that view), but instead we should try to check what is the inserted card and take an action if the inserted card is displayed in the list above, if not, we should display a message that inserted card doesn't match any of the known keycards for this keypair.",
